          <p>The components of the quadrupled-indexed amplicon libraries. A specific DNA region is amplified using fusion and tagged locus-specific primers, also known as “indexed fusion primers”, to produce a fusion amplicon. Then iTru adapters are incorporated using limited cycle PCR with i5- and i7-indexed primers to make the complete double stranded DNA library. Internal indexes and outer i5/i7 indexes are represented as well as the set of primers used.</p>
